National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location: San Luis Obispo, CA
Accident Number: WPR15CA074
Date & Time: 01/03/2015, 1351 PST
Registration: N171L
Aircraft: WACO CLASSIC AIRCRAFT YMF F5C
Aircraft Damage: Substantial
Defining Event: Nose over/nose down
Injuries: 2 None
Flight Conducted Under: Part 91: General Aviation - Personal
 Analysis The pilot reported that while rolling out about 30 to 40 mph in the tailwheel equipped airplane for the full stop landing, the airplane made a sudden stop and nosed over.
The airplane sustained substantial damage to the aft fuselage and tail section during the landing sequence.
The passenger reported in a written statement that he accidentally applied the brakes during the landing roll.
The pilot reported no preimpact mechanical malfunctions or failures with the airplane that would have precluded normal operation.
Probable Cause and Findings The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be: The accidental application of the brakes by the passenger during landing roll which resulted in the airplane nosing over.
